          "correct_option": "A",
          "explanation": "$\\text{cosec } \\frac{2\\pi}{3} = \\frac{1}{\\sin 120^\\circ} = \\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{2}{3}\\sqrt{3}$. $\\sec \\frac{2\\pi}{3} = \\frac{1}{\\cos 120^\\circ} = -2$. Thus, $-2 + \\frac{2}{3}\\sqrt{3} = a + b\\sqrt{3}$, so $a = -2$.",
